name: HubSpot Marketing
description: Add a HubSpot Instance to connect your existing HubSpot account to the Marketing Hub, allowing you to manage accounts, campaigns, contacts, leads etc. across multiple Marketing Elements. You will need your HubSpot account information to add an instance.
configDescription: If you do not have a HubSpot account, you can create one at HubSpot Signup

configuration.name: Hubspot Contacts Property Fields Configuration
configuration.description: The Hubspot properties to retrieve with each contact retrieved from Hubspot

configuration.name: Authentication Type
configuration.description: Type of authentication to be used while connecting to Hubspot

configuration.name: HubSpot Client ID
configuration.description: OAuth Client ID for the requesting HubSpot app.

configuration.name: Hubspot API Key
configuration.description: Hubspot API Key to be used for authentication

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: HubSpot Portal ID

configuration.name: HubSpot Scopes
configuration.description:
Scope(s) of the requesting HubSpot app. In new OAuth2 applications, scopes have to match what
  was set up in their OAuth application exactly and paid Marketing Hubspotters can request all application scopes.

configuration.name: Create Bulk Properties for Migration
configuration.description: Setting this to true will create custom properties in Hubspot which are used during bulk uploads

configuration.name: User Email Address
configuration.description: Email Address of Logged In User when Using OAuth2

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event Notification Subscription ID
configuration.description: The subscription ID for the webhook events subscription

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Used for how often to poll the application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Resources Configuration
configuration.description: Event Poller Resources Configuration. The configuration is defined via JSON, an example of which is as follows - {"contacts": { "url": "/hubs/marketing/contacts?where=lastmodifieddate='${date}'","idField": "vid","filterByUpdatedDate": true,"datesConfiguration": {"updatedDateField": "properties.lastmodifieddate","updatedDateFormat": "milliseconds","createdDateField": "properties.createdate","createdDateFormat": "milliseconds"},"createdCheckTolerance": 10}}

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

objects.name: accounts
objects.description: Accounts in Hubspot Marketing are mapped to Companies. Accounts allows you to manage your company data in HubSpot. Accounts in HubSpot can represent any type of organization.

objects.name: accountsProperties
objects.description: company properties are used to store specific information for your company records.  HubSpot has several default properties, but you can also create custom properties to store any data you need for your company records.  Company properties can also be used to filter companies that show up in your view when viewing your records in HubSpot.

objects.name: accountsPropertygroups
objects.description: company property group. Property groups allow you to more easily manage properties in a given portal and make contact records easier to parse for the user.

objects.name: activities
objects.description: Activities is mapped to Engagements. They used to store data from CRM actions, including notes, tasks, meetings, and calls. Engagements should be associated with at least one contact record, and optionally other contacts, deals, and a company record.

objects.name: campaigns
objects.description: For a given portal, return all campaign IDs sorted by recent activity associated with the portal

objects.name: campaignsActivities
objects.description: Returns all of the event definitions in a given portal. Events can be created in-app, or dynamically

objects.name: contacts
objects.description: Contacts are the fundamental building block to HubSpot - they store lead-specific data that makes it possible to leverage much of the functionality in HubSpot, from marketing automation, to lead scoring to smart content.
objects.notes: -- Must pass `useBatchUpload=true` parameter to leverage nativeBulkUpload. Native bulk upload does not validate success of upload, this is a limitation of the Hubspot service for leads & contacts

objects.name: contactsActivities
objects.description: Get an engagement (a task or activity) on an contact in HubSpot. This data is often used for per rep productivity reporting or integration with other back-office tools.

objects.name: contactsLists
objects.description: Return the contact lists for a portal

objects.name: contactsProperties
objects.description: Contact properties are used to store specific information for each of your contact records. HubSpot has several default contact properties, but you can also create custom properties to store whatever data you need for your contact records. Properties are used as the criteria for contact lists, to segment your contacts, and also as the starting criteria for workflows

objects.name: contactsPropertygroups
objects.description: contact groups 0of the contact property groups for a portal.

objects.name: contactsWorkflows
objects.description: Get workflows a contact is currently enrolled in. This is particularly useful for integrations that take contact data and display them in a different interface.

objects.name: deals
objects.description: The Deals API, along with the Companies API, has been exposed to allow for easy integration with the HubSpot CRM objects. A couple of use cases the API can support: Creating a client in a project management system when a deal is marked as closed won. Syncing Deal data with a legacy CRM. Executing advanced revenue reporting in a 3rd party reporting platform

objects.name: filesArchive
objects.description: Archive an existing file from a particular HubSpot portal. Archiving will not hard delete a file from a portal, but will remove that file from the HubSpot user interface

objects.name: filesCdnFiles
objects.description: Permanently delete a file and all related data and thumbnails from file manager. Once if we did this we cannot restore the file!!

objects.name: folders
objects.description: metadata of Folders in file system

objects.name: lists
objects.description: Contact Lists are used to segment contacts into groups. There are two main types of lists, dynamic (usually referred to as smart lists) and static. Dynamic lists automatically add or remove contacts, based on the list criteria. List membership is managed automatically, and is updated whenever data changes for a contact, so it is not possible to manually remove or add contacts to a dynamic list. Static lists can also automatically include contacts, but the criteria is only evaluated when the list is created. After the list is created, the list memebership will not change unless contacts are manually added or removed from the list.

objects.name: listsContacts
objects.description: Users of HubSpot generally use lists to group like contacts together for marketing automation, but for the purposes of integration, you will likely want to create a list before you get contacts from it.

objects.name: workflows
objects.description: workflows are one of the most essential pieces to the HubSpot marketing software, because it, along with Contacts and email, is at the heart of marketing automation. Using workflows, users can set up sophisticated marketing automation campaigns that rely on triggering relevant and timely actions (like emails) for contacts in their database.
